text:
Q: How to set up web clip icons in &quot;Google apps script&quot; A: <p>You can set the apple-touch-icon meta tag or any other meta tag dynamically in your GAS web app. Keep in mind that this is a workaround and not a direct solution due to GAS's limitations in directly manipulating HTML head elements.</p>
<pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;App Title&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1&quot;&gt;
  &lt;!-- #INSERT_APPLE_TOUCH_ICON# --&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;!-- Your app content goes here --&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>Google Apps Script</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>function doGet() {
  var template = HtmlService.createTemplateFromFile('templatefile');

  // Replace the placeholder with the actual meta tag
  var appleTouchIconTag = '&lt;link rel=&quot;apple-touch-icon&quot; href=&quot;iconUrl.png&quot;&gt;';
  template.appleTouchIconTag = appleTouchIconTag;

  return template.evaluate();
}
</code></pre>
